ANIME.JS — ANIMATION ENGINE

Anime.js provides advanced tweening and timeline capabilities. In Remotion, use it to COMPUTE values per frame rather than running timeline playback.

KEY CONCEPT: Do NOT let anime.js run its own timeline. Instead, use anime.set() or compute values manually based on useCurrentFrame().

USEFUL FUNCTIONS:
- anime.set(targets, properties) — instantly set CSS properties
- anime.stagger(value, options) — generate staggered delay values: anime.stagger(100) returns [0, 100, 200, ...]
- anime.path(svgPath) — get path coordinates for motion-along-path

EASING FUNCTIONS (use for interpolate alternatives):
- 'easeInOutQuad', 'easeInOutCubic', 'easeOutElastic', 'easeOutBounce'
- 'spring(mass, stiffness, damping, velocity)'

IN REMOTION PATTERN:
```tsx
const frame = useCurrentFrame();
const staggerDelays = anime.stagger(5, { from: 'center' });
const elements = items.map((item, i) => {
  const itemFrame = frame - (staggerDelays[i] as number);
  const opacity = interpolate(itemFrame, [0, 15], [0, 1], { extrapolateLeft: 'clamp', extrapolateRight: 'clamp' });
  return <div style={{ opacity }}>{item}</div>;
});
```
